node.text:
Today we celebrate 57 years of Padrón Cigars. We would like to thank all those who have helped us get to where we are today. We are grateful to my father and Family patriarch, Jose O. Padrón, for setting an example for us to follow, and his unwavering dedication to producing the world’s finest cigars. My mother Flory was his pillar of strength, always supporting his endeavors, and the risks he took. She understood the road to success required selflessness and determination. Both of them made many sacrifices in those early days; sacrifices that became the foundation of our business. We are grateful to our loyal and dedicated employees, in Nicaragua and Miami, without whom none of this would be possible. Producing the finest cigars requires attention to detail at every level. Their understanding of our mission is key to ensuring that we focus on quality above all else. 

Thank you to the countless loyal customers who have stood by our brand and products for all of these years. My family and I accept the responsibility of maintaining the standards that you are accustomed to from our products, and understand that your support has to be earned and maintained over the course of time.
 
Padrón Cigars was founded as a family business and remains so to this day. Thank you to my family members Flory, Orlando, Elizabeth, Lisette, Rudy, Gabriel, Elizabeth, Marcos, Jeffrey, Jessica, Kimberly, Jorge Luis, Alfonso and Andres, who continue to work in the business. My father would be very proud to see what his family learned from him and how we honor him and his traditions.
 
We look forward to many more years of producing the world’s finest cigars and sharing them with those who understand and appreciate the dedication it takes to manufacture them. 
 
Going strong and growing at 57!

Jorge Padrón
President

#teampadron #padron #cigars #padroncigars #padroning
